by Hatsunia » Fri Dec 18, 2020 11:25 am

There was a collapse and technological reversion in 2066, with many areas of the US being led by warlords until the mid-22nd century. Before Wexas formed in the late 24th century, there was the Aggies Duchy (named after an old football team). A new religion formed centered around the marshland, which came into conflict with the Catholic Longhorn Duchy. The Longhorns declared war on the Aggies but lost. The Aggies Duchy, later known as the Duchy of Houston, would expand its territory even further before becoming the Kingdom of Wexas, being all the wetland areas of Texas.

AN: Tohorin is named after a mythological sun goddess. There was another rival deity named Terasu but they hid in a cave instead of battling sea monsters like Tohorin did, according to the myth, and Terasu became the Regent of the Night, envying Tohorin's position.

The flag represents the homeland (blue circle) surrounded by four cardinal directions.

north - black (underworld)
south - blue (sky/sea)
east - red (sunrise)
west - yellow (sunset)

by Leskya » Sat Dec 19, 2020 2:43 pm

Hatsunia is predominantly a temperate country, although the north and south experience more extreme variations in weather and climate. Northern Hatsunia is a more humid, continental climate, akin to Central and Eastern Europe. Meanwhile, the south varies between a Meditteranean climate, with hot summers and mild winters, and a subtropical climate, defined by humid summers and very mild winters with heavy rains. Due to this range of climates, Hatsunia possesses both temperate and broadleaf forests.
